under $1,200 available.  &UR; BY BECKY WARING &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; COMPUTING _ &LR;  Q: What should be my top priorities when shopping for
a notebook computer? And what will I have to pay for a decent one?
</P>
<P>
   A: Notebook PCs (also called laptops) can be had for less than
$1,000, but to get one that provides a satisfying computing
experience, you're probably looking at $1,500 minimum. The two
things that make the biggest difference between a good notebook and
a mediocre one are the technology used in the display, and the
weight of the computer. Notebooks costing less than $1,500
generally have dual-scan displays, while more expensive machines
have TFT active displays. The active display is clear and bright
regardless of the viewing angle. With a dual-scan display, you have
to look directly at the screen or it fades.  &UR; Q&AMP;A COLUMN BY &LR; 
 &UR; DAVID EINSTEIN &LR;
</P>
