Street in San Francisco, has given his business a jump start by
increasingly selling items not over the counter but to EBay users
throughout the world.  &UR; BY DAVID LAZARUS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; GAP _ &LR;  The back-to-school season came in with a pained whimper at
Gap Inc., as same-store sales at all four of the company's
divisions declined during August, the retailer reported yesterday.
</P>
<P>
   Companywide, same-store sales, or sales at stores open at least
a year, plummeted 14 percent against August 1999, about twice the
shortfall expected by analysts. Leading the plunge was the
low-price Old Navy chain, which saw same-store sales tumble a
stunning 24 to 26 percent. (Gap provides ranges, rather than
specific numbers, for sales of its individual chains.)  &UR; BY CAROL &LR; 
 &UR; EMERT &LR;
</P>
