   ``A Walk in the Clouds,'' ABC Saturday at 8: Keanu Reeves stars
in this 1995 film about a married salesman who agrees to pose as a
pregnant woman's husband in postwar California.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Rockford Files: Friends and Foul Play,'' CBS Saturday at
9: Stuart Margolin, who plays Angel, directed James Garner and a
cast of regulars in this so-so 1996 case. But there's a bonus:
David Proval, aka Richie April of ``The Sopranos,'' has a small
role.
</P>
<P>
   ``Saturday Night Live,'' NBC Saturday at 11:30: You have to let
your teen-age daughters stay up for this one, as Joshua Jackson of
``Dawson's Creek'' hosts, with musical guest 'N Sync. Rerun.
</P>
<P>
   Jerry Lewis Labor Day Telethon, various channels, Sunday at 9:
Yes, it's time again for that end-of-summer ritual to benefit the
fight against muscular dystrophy. Jerry's guests in his 35th year
include Regis Philbin, Sting and Christina Aguilera. The show
continues until 6 p.m. Monday.
</P>
