</P>
<P>
   BETTER-JOBS (San Francisco) - As good as the economy is and as
wonderful as the job market is, a lot of people still are
struggling. They really are trying to land a better job, but
nothing seems to be going their way. If you're one of them and have
no idea why the world is passing you by, consider six possible
causes. By DAVE MURPHY.
</P>
<P>
   STORYTELLING-WEB-SITE (San Francisco) _ A television actor, a
computer magazine editor and the CEO of a Menlo Park-based software
company may have created a Web site formula for the next generation
of entertainment. It is a new venture called Alien Voices, a
storytelling site that mixes the elements of a drama with a
game-like interactive feature. By RICHARD PAOLI.
</P>
<P>
   WINE (San Francisco) _ Sebastiani Vineyards Inc. has agreed to
sell its high-volume, lower-end wine division and its marketing
unit to San Francisco-based The Wine Group Inc. as part of its
effort to concentrate on premium wines. By VICTORIA COLLIVER and
JENNY STRASBURG.
