</P>
<P>
   TV-WEEKEND _ Weekend TV preview for Labor Day weekend. (Kloer,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 18.
</P>
<P>
   CHILD-STARS _ I've always wondered why any parent would let
their child go into show business. Sure, the potential for huge
paydays is tempting. But is the price that must be paid for that
possible fortune worth it? Child stars, for instance, are often
robbed of a normal childhood. Growing up is hard enough. Imagine
having to do it in front of millions of people watching your every
move or snickering about every goofy-looking pimple you get. The
pressure to perform is also insanely intense. Many adult actors
can't even take the heat and often resort to drugs and alcohol to
cope. Just think what it's like for a kid to overhear a producer
angrily talking about low ratings and possible cancellation.
(Thompson, Palm Beach Post)
</P>
<P>
   MOVIE NEWS AND REVIEWS
</P>
<P>
   MOVIE-GREENBERG _ Since she has been toiling for the past 12
years on The Life and Times of Hank Greenberg, an affectionate
documentary tribute to the first Jewish baseball star,
writer-director Aviva Kempner could not have intended it as a
metaphor for the current barrier-shattering campaign bid of
Orthodox Jewish Sen. Joseph Lieberman. (Erstein, Plam Beach Post).
35.
