</P>
<P>
   SYDNEY _ With only a fortnight to go until the Sydney Olympic
Games begin, the Australian government has taken the controversial
step of banning visits by United Nations human-rights inspectors in
the wake of recent criticism of the country's treatment of its
Aboriginal people and of asylum-seekers....By Kathy Marks, The
Independent &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (TIMELY for upcoming Olympics, Sydney) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (375 words) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; `PEACEMAKER' QADDAFI'S CURIOUS DEALINGS ACROSS AFRICA, ASIA &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; QADDAFI-INTRIGUE-FISK-INDEPENDENT &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   BEIRUT _ Muammar Qaddafi must sometimes find it difficult to
remember which ``liberation'' movement he has supported and which
he has ignored. Ten years ago, Sierre Leone's Foday Sankoh _ famous
for his group's leg, ear, hand and lip amputations _ trained in
Libya alongside Charles Taylor, Liberia's gangland boss-made
president. In May, Qaddafi sent a delegation to Sierre Leone to
work for the release of U.N. staff taken hostage by rebels....By
Robert Fisk, The Independent &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (ATTN: Commentary Editors) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (650 words) &QL;
</P>
