<P>
   &UR; THE `WHORING' OF AMERICAN POLITICS &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; `PIMP'-POLITICS-USA-775&AMP;add-INDEPENDENT &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ It is an odd time to be a dissenter in America.
The economy is booming. No Americans are dying in foreign wars.
Unemployment is down, and so is crime. And yet the dissent is
there, and it is being felt across an extraordinary range of public
opinion. For all of their disparate agendas, however, there is one
unifying theme binding these dissenting voices: a sense of outrage
at the corruption of America's political system....By Andrew
Gumbel, The Independent &QL;
</P>
