 (Editors: All times are Eastern Time unless otherwise specified.
Please check local listings for time and channel.) 
 By JOEL BROWN 
 c.2000 Joel Brown 
<TEXT>
<P>
   With the Sydney Olympics just over a week away, expect a lot of
shows to take a look at Australia. Likely to be among the best of
them is ``Australia: Beyond the Fatal Shore,'' a six-part
documentary by Time magazine art critic Robert Hughes, a native
Australian. It debuts tonight at 9 on most PBS stations. Hughes
wrote the bestselling history ``The Fatal Shore.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Beyond'' seems to mean a further linking of the disparate
elements of the culture, from the complex relationship between
whites and aborigines to the equally complex relationship between
whites and their own pleasure-seeking instincts. Hughes is good
company _ if this were a movie, Albert Finney might play him. This
may be more interesting than many of the Games themselves.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; HIGHLIGHTS &LR;  &QL;
