<P>
   BLACK-CEMETERY _ The city's efforts to get a memorial for the
mostly black victims of the 1928 hurricane buried in a mass grave
off Tamarind have collapsed because of an incomplete grant
application. The state grant the city had hoped to get would have
helped pay the more than $200,000 asking price for land owned by a
pesticide company. (Van Sickler, Palm Beach Post).
</P>
