<HEADLINE>
&HT;     NEW LEGAL HASSLES FOR RAIDERS RECEIVER 
</HEADLINE>
   &HT;     (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 &HT;     By FRANK BLACKMAN  
 &HT;     c.2000 San Francisco Examiner  
<TEXT>
<P>
   ALAMEDA, Calif. _ Andre Rison has a new legal problem.
</P>
<P>
   On Tuesday, the Kansas City Star reported that the Raiders wide
receiver owes more than $34,000 in child support for his 2-year-old
son.
</P>
<P>
   Rison arrived here facing a trial on the alleged theft of a
$1,000 tape recorder. Then it was announced he had been indicted
for allegedly writing $158,000 in bad checks to a jewelry store.
</P>
<P>
   Marilynn Knipp, a director with the Missouri Department of
Social Services, said the state would file in California to garnish
Rison's wages.
</P>
<P>
   ``It'll be resolved,'' Rison said. ``My attorney is handling
it.''
</P>
<P>
   Rison was asked what he would say in his defense when people say
he is a bad guy.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm a Raider,'' Rison said, laughing. ``I don't worry about
what people say about me. I go out and do my job. The team's been
looking at me, not only as a teammate, but a friend, also.''
</P>
<P>
   Rison believes he's been portrayed unfairly.
</P>
<P>
   ``Very unfair,'' he said. ``I'm a beautiful father, and I live a
beautiful life. I'm not saying I've been a saint, and I'm not
saying I'm perfect, and I'm not saying I'm wrong. But I am a
Raider.''
</P>
<P>
   Rison was cut by the Chiefs before signing with Oakland last
month.
</P>
<P>
   Despite his legal problems, Rison will get an opportunity to
take his shots on the field on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't think it's going to distract the team,'' coach Jon
Gruden said. ``I worry more about it distracting Andre Rison. We
will continue to support him and gather our information and react
accordingly. For the time being, we support him, and hopefully we
can get these things resolved so that he can just concentrate on
playing football. That's why he's here.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-08-31-00 1933EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
