<P>
   AIDSKIDS (Phoenix) - More kids born with HIV or AIDS are defying
previous odds and are entering into their pre-teen or teenage
years. Of the 60 kids who are being treated in the Phoenix area for
AIDS, 10 are 10 or over. Many of them were once told they would
only live a few years. While the plight of 14 year old Stephanie
Ray, who captured a lot of attention, it's pretty typical for AIDS
families to have complicated family arrangements and crises. And
with more of them living longer, they are making new demands on
schools, government agencies and insurance companies. By MAUREEN
WEST. Story will move in the ``A'' category.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
