 &UR; NETWORTH:  &LR; How much should a buyer expect to pay for a house in San
Francisco when there are multiple offers? If there are six to eight
bids, the winning buyer is likely to pay 20 to 30 percent above the
asking price, according to a new study by San Francisco real estate
broker John M. Lee. Lee says he conducted the survey because the
old rules of thumb no longer apply in the Bay Area, where many
homes are deliberately underpriced to create a feeding frenzy among
buyers. Column by Kathleen Pender
