   (NYT3) UNDATED -- Aug. 31, 2000 -- OBIT-ANDERS-B&AMP;W -- Arthur F.
Anders, an officer of the U.S. Navy gunboat Panay who took command
despite serious wounds after Japanese warplanes attacked it on the
Yangtze River in China in 1937, died on Sunday at his home in
Rancho Bernardo, Calif. He was 96. Anders in a file photo circa
1930. (The New York Times)
