   (NYT2) UNDATED -- Aug. 31, 2000 -- OBIT-MARCA-RELLI-B&AMP;W --
Conrad Marca-Relli, an American artist linked to Abstract
Expressionism and known for making large patchwork collages of cut
pieces of canvas, died Tuesday at his home in Parma, Italy. He was
87. Marca-Relli in a 1976 file photo. (The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT1) GETTYSBURG, Pa. -- Aug. 31, 2000 -- GETTYSBURG-MUSEUM-1
-- The National Park Service recommends on its Web site that
visitors to the Gettysburg National Military Park spend at least
four hours touring the battlefield and museum, ``though an entire
day is more desirable.'' As understatements go, this is a keeper.
