<P>
   (NYT39) HERMOSA BEACH, Costa Rica -- Aug. 31, 2000 --
COSTARICA-ECOTOURISM-2 -- Costa Rica was a pioneer in the field of
eco-tourism in the 1980s, turning its lush landscape of rumbling
volcanoes, high cloud forests, rushing mountain streams, vibrant
rainforests and gorgeous deserted beaches into a nature-lover's
vacation paradise. In the past decade, the Central American
hideaway has put action into the mix. Visitors can raft through
raging whitewater streams, mountain bike through dense forests, and
even kayak along unspoiled rocky beaches. (Mike Williams/Cox News
Service)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT38) HERMOSA BEACH, Costa Rica -- Aug. 31, 2000 --
